.</span><hr size=1> Everquest is a thing of the past for me, but i will always have fond memories of the game. I also plan on trying EQ2.<br>
<br>
<br>
One thing that bothers me about EQ2 and other games that are trying to copy Everquest's success. I don't think they know what was so great about the game. It was basically a perfect vision of my childhood fantasies!<br>
<br>
EQ's depictions of dragons and warriors, damsels and elves, dwarfs and hobbits were better then anything i could imagine reading tolkien!  Actually EQ was a perfect merger of my D&amp;D and Tolkienesque dreams of my youth!<br>
<br>
I have played many breathtaking 3d games and these days incredible graphics are a dime a dozen. Its how the artistry makes the player feel that is important!<br>
Nothing can compare to my first visons of Norrath. I will always remember strolling through the misty hills of steamfont and veiwing the wily windmills. My first meetings with the hearty barbarians and the disgusting trolls filled me with wonder. My first view of the treehouse in the Karanas or my first meeting with a cyclops made me feel small and mortal.<br>
The wonderful music in qeynos hills and rivervale filled my heart with glee. Wandering around neriak and lavastorm chilled me to the bone. Spending the day in everfrost was uplifting , while spending the evening in Guk filled me with dread.<br>
<br>
Everquest was full of the things we dreamed of reading all of our fantasy classics. It nailed it. <br>
I don't think they can duplicate that feeling.<br>
So far the screenshots for EQ 2 remind me of doom. UGGHHH!<br>
<br>
So whatever sony does for its new endeavor, i hope they remain true to thier Vision(tm).<br>
The Vision was the perfect recreation of my childhood fantasies.<br>
